ğŸ’¡ Definition

An Apex Trigger is a piece of code that automatically executes when a data event occurs (insert, update, delete, etc.) on a Salesforce Object.

Think of it as:

â€œWhen something happens to a record â†’ do this additional logic.â€

ğŸ§© STEP 2 â€“ Why We Use Triggers
Use Case	Example
Auto-populate a field	Set â€œDescriptionâ€ whenever an Account is created
