ğŸ§  STEP 1 â€“ What is LWC

Lightning Web Components (LWC) = Salesforceâ€™s modern front-end framework built on standard JavaScript, HTML, and CSS.

It lets you create fast, reusable UI components that talk to Salesforce data using Apex or built-in wire adapters.

Think of LWC as the â€œvisual faceâ€ of your Apex logic.

âš™ï¸ STEP 2 â€“ Why LWC (Compared to Aura)
Feature	LWC	Aura
Based on Modern Web Standards	âœ… Yes	âŒ Older Framework
Speed & Performance	âš¡ Fast (JavaScript Engine)	ğŸ¢ Slower
Developer Experience	VS Code + Modules	XML heavy
Recommended by Salesforce (2025 onward)	âœ… Yes	âš ï¸ Legacy

So â†’ always build new UIs using LWC.

ğŸ§© STEP 3 â€“ LWC File Structure

When you create an LWC component, Salesforce generates three main files:

File	Purpose
helloWorld.html	Template (UI structure)
helloWorld.js	JavaScript logic (variables, events)
helloWorld.js-meta.xml	Metadata file (defines where component can appear â€” Record Page, App, etc.)

Summary of How It Works Internally

- Salesforce injects recordId into your component when itâ€™s placed on a record page.

- LWC detects that recordId changed.

- Because you prefixed $recordId ($ - reactive variable) in your @wire parameters â†’ the wire function re-runs automatically.

- getRecord fetches new data â†’ updates the bound variable (this.record).

- UI updates automatically.

Example Quiz (interview tip)

ğŸ§© Question: What happens if you remove $ from $recordId inside your @wire decorator?
Answer: The record ID becomes static; @wire will not re-run when the record changes, and the component wonâ€™t refresh on navigation.


SOSL & SOQL:

| Type     | Full Form                         | Purpose                                                   |
| -------- | --------------------------------- | --------------------------------------------------------- |
| **SOQL** | Salesforce Object Query Language  | Fetch records from **one object (and its relationships)** |
| **SOSL** | Salesforce Object Search Language | Search a text term across **multiple objects** at once    |

| Scenario                             | Use SOQL | Use SOSL |
| ------------------------------------ | -------- | -------- |
| Need data from one object            | âœ…        | âŒ        |
| Need to filter on field values       | âœ…        | âŒ        |
| Need to search text across objects   | âŒ        | âœ…        |
| Searching a keyword typed by user    | âŒ        | âœ…        |
| Display related records in LWC table | âœ…        | âŒ        |

ğŸ§  STEP 1 â€“ Understand What â€œImperative Apex Callâ€ Means

In @wire, Salesforce handles the call automatically.

In an imperative call, you decide when to call Apex â€” usually after a button click or user input.

This gives you more control (great for search, filters, save/update operations).

Think:

â€œWhen the user clicks Search â†’ fetch data from Apex manually.â€
