ğŸ’¡ What is @track in LWC?

In LWC, @track is used to make a variable reactive â€” meaning if that variableâ€™s value changes, the UI automatically updates to reflect the new data.

Think of it like telling LWC:

â€œHey Salesforce, keep an eye on this variable â€” if it changes, re-render the template.â€

If we wont use any decorator what happens-

| Data Type | Without Decorator                   | With `@track` | Behavior                                                           |
| --------- | ----------------------------------- | ------------- | ------------------------------------------------------------------ |
| `String`  | âœ… Reactive                          | âœ… Reactive    | Works either way                                                   |
| `Number`  | âœ… Reactive                          | âœ… Reactive    | Works either way                                                   |
| `Boolean` | âœ… Reactive                          | âœ… Reactive    | Works either way                                                   |
| `Array`   | âš ï¸ Not reactive on internal changes | âœ… Reactive    | Add/remove elements wonâ€™t re-render unless reassigned              |
| `Object`  | âš ï¸ Not reactive on internal changes | âœ… Reactive    | Inner property changes wonâ€™t reflect unless `@track` or reassigned |
------------------------------
ALL KINDS OF DECORATOR IN LWC-
| Decorator | Meaning                                          | Used For                        | Reactivity                           | Example                             |
| --------- | ------------------------------------------------ | ------------------------------- | ------------------------------------ | ----------------------------------- |
| `@track`  | Make property reactive (esp. for objects/arrays) | Internal variables              | âœ… UI auto-updates when value changes | `@track user = { name: 'Poorvi' };` |
| `@api`    | Make property/method public                      | Parent â†’ Child communication    | âš™ï¸ Controlled by parent              | `@api message;`                     |
| `@wire`   | Wire Apex or Salesforce data                     | Auto-fetching data from backend | âœ… Auto-updates when param changes    | `@wire(getAccounts) accounts;`      |

| Situation                     | What to Use                 |
| ----------------------------- | --------------------------- |
| Simple string/number          | Nothing                     |
| List of records               | `@track` or reassign array  |
| Object with nested fields     | `@track` or reassign object |
| Data shared with parent       | `@api`                      |
| Data fetched from Apex or LDS | `@wire`                     |
