ğŸŒ What Is NavigationMixin in LWC?

The NavigationMixin is a Salesforce-provided JavaScript mixin that allows your Lightning Web Component to navigate the user to different pages â€”
just like clicking a link or button in the Salesforce UI.

Think of it as:

â€œA built-in helper that lets my LWC open other pages inside Salesforce Lightning Experience â€” record pages, list views, URLs, files, etc.â€

âš™ï¸ Why We Need It

Normally, JavaScript in a browser canâ€™t directly control Salesforceâ€™s internal navigation (record pages, setup pages, etc.),
because those routes are handled inside the Lightning framework â€” not normal URLs.
import { NavigationMixin } from 'lightning/navigation';

export default class AccountSearch extends NavigationMixin(LightningElement) {

this[NavigationMixin.Navigate](pageReference);

ğŸ§  What Is a Page Reference?

A Page Reference is simply a JavaScript object that describes what and where you want to navigate.

{
  type: 'standard__recordPage',
  attributes: {
    recordId: '001xxxxxxxxxxxx',
    objectApiName: 'Account',
    actionName: 'view'
  }
}
| Key             | Meaning                                                       |
| --------------- | ------------------------------------------------------------- |
| `type`          | What kind of page to open (record page, list view, URL, etc.) |
| `recordId`      | The Salesforce record ID                                      |
| `objectApiName` | Object name (`Account`, `Contact`, etc.)                      |
| `actionName`    | What to do â€” `view`, `edit`, or `clone`                       |
-----------------------------------------------
â­ What does dispatchEvent() do? (Layman's Explanation)

Think of it like this:

ğŸ‘‰ A child LWC wants to tell the parent LWC that something happened

So the child sends a signal/message.

That signal is the Custom Event.

dispatchEvent() allows a child LWC to notify the parent that something happened (like button clicked, record created, etc).
â­ Real World Analogy

ğŸ‘ Child = ringing a doorbell
ğŸ‘ dispatchEvent = pressing the bell button
ğŸ‘ Parent = hears the ring and responds